title: District Scholars Program
Description:: The District Scholars Program is open to full - time, first - year undergraduate students at George Washington University.  You must be a resident of the District and qualify for the D.C. Tuition Assistance Grant to be eligible for this award.

title: Honors at Entrance Scholarship/Early Admission
Description:: The Honors at Entrance Scholarship/Early Admission is available to entering freshmen at the University of Utah.  This award is based on GPA, satisfactory academic progress and ACT/SAT scores.  You must be a Utah resident.  This award is renewable with a maintained minimum GPA of 3.7 and at least 20 credit hours completed each semester.

title: Berkeley College Presidential Scholarship
Description:: The Berkeley College Presidential Scholarship is available to high school seniors entering Berkeley College.  You must demonstrate a high level of academic achievement to be considered for this award.

title: Young Patriots Essay Contest
Description:: The Young Patriots Essay Contest is open to high school students.  To be considered, you must submit an essay on the following topic:  "Are international free trade agreements in the best interest of the United States? Why or why not?"
